            <entry xml:id="entry_cʼītī" xml:lang="os">
                <form xml:lang="os-x-iron" type="lemma"><orth>cʼītī</orth></form>
                <form xml:lang="os-x-digor" type="dialectal"><orth>cʼete</orth></form>
                <sense><sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>ледник</q>
                        </abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>glacier</q>
                        </abv:tr></sense><sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>глетчер</q>
                        </abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>ice hill</q>
                        </abv:tr></sense></sense>
                <abv:exampleGrp>
                    <abv:example>
                        <quote>cʼitītæ jæ færsty badync īx-zæjtæj</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>глетчеры по сторонам застыли ледяными лавинами</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>glaciers froze in ice avalanches on the sides</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Коста"/><biblScope>63</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                    <abv:example>
                        <quote>ʒæbīdyry sænyk cʼītījyl bazzad</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>козленок тура остался на леднике</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>tur's goatlet stayed on the glacier</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><biblScope xml:lang="ru">из песни</biblScope><biblScope xml:lang="en"
                                >from the song</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                    <abv:example>
                        <quote>mæ zærdæ fyrcinæj ryzti, k˳y skastæn næ cʼītīǵyn xæxtæm</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>мое сердце дрожало от радости, когда я взглянул на наши покрытые
                                ледниками горы</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>my heart throbbed with joy when I looked at our glacier-covered
                                mountains</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Коста"/><biblScope>31</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                    <abv:example xml:lang="os-x-digor">
                        <usg><lang/></usg>
                        <quote>fæjnerdigæj cʼetetæ zinnuncæ</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>со всех сторон видны ледники</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>glaciers are visible from all sides</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Iræf"/><biblScope>26</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                    <abv:example xml:lang="os-x-digor">
                        <usg><lang/></usg>
                        <quote>сʼetejæn ... æ xodæ tajuj, tæʒuj æ usqæj</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>шапка глетчера тает, каплет с его плеча</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>glacier's hat melts, it is dripping from its shoulder</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Sozur"/><biblScope>11</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                    <abv:example>
                        <quote>zalty mīt æmæ ænūsy cʼītī</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>небывалый снегопад („заловский снег и вечный глетчер“)</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>unprecedented snowfall (“%iZal%i, i.e. very heavy snow and eternal
                                glacier”)</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_ЮОПам."/><biblScope>I 69, 70,
                                134</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                </abv:exampleGrp>
                <etym xml:lang="ru">Как и другие термины, связанные с высокогорной природой, идет не
                    из иранского, а кавказского языкового мира (ср. <ref type="xr"
                        target="#entry_zæj"/> ‘лавина’, <ref type="xr" target="#entry_kʼæj"/>
                    ‘плитняк’, <ref type="xr" target="#entry_sykʼi"/> ‘серна’ и др.). Ос. %icʼītī%i
                    | %icʼete%i безупречно отвечает <mentioned xml:lang="ka"><lang/>
                        <w>m-cʼveti</w>
                        <gloss><q>каплющий</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ka"
                        ><w/></mentioned>, ср. <mentioned xml:lang="ka"><lang/>
                        <w>cʼveti</w>
                        <gloss><q>капля</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ka"
                            ><w>cʼveta</w>
                        <gloss><q>капать</q></gloss></mentioned> (тающие, „каплющие“ ледники дают,
                    как известно, начало горным рекам). Выпадение %iv%i перед %ii%i, в закономерно,
                    ср. <ref type="xr" target="#entry_ḱʼīrī"/> | %ikʼere%i ‘пирог’← <mentioned
                        xml:lang="ka"><lang/>
                        <w>kʼveri</w></mentioned>, <ref type="xr" target="#entry_kʼela"/> ‘скамья’ ←
                        <mentioned xml:lang="xmf"><lang/>
                        <w>kʼvela</w></mentioned>, <ref type="xr" target="#entry_xīd"/> | %ixed%i
                    ‘пот’ ← <mentioned xml:lang="x-oldirn"><lang/>
                        <w>xvaida-</w></mentioned>, <ref type="xr" target="#entry_xī"/> | %iхе%i
                    ‘свой’ ← <mentioned xml:lang="x-oldirn"><lang/>
                        <w>xvai-</w></mentioned>, <ref type="xr" target="#entry_xīstær"/> |
                    %ixestær%i ‘старший’ = <mentioned xml:lang="sog"><lang/>
                        <w>xveštar</w></mentioned> и др.%n<bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_ОЯФ_I"
                            /><biblScope>51, 325</biblScope></bibl>.</etym>
                <etym xml:lang="en">Like other terms connected with mountain nature, this word does
                    not trace back to Iranian but to Caucasian languages (cf. <ref type="xr"
                        target="#entry_zæj"/> ‘avalanche’, <ref type="xr" target="#entry_kʼæj"/>
                    ‘flagstone’, <ref type="xr" target="#entry_sykʼi"/> ‘chamois’ etc.). Ossetic
                    %icʼītī%i | %icʼete%i perfectly corresponds to <mentioned xml:lang="ka"><lang/>
                        <w>m-cʼveti</w>
                        <gloss><q>dripping</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ka"
                        ><w/></mentioned>, cf. <mentioned xml:lang="ka"><lang/>
                        <w>cʼveti</w>
                        <gloss><q>drop (n)</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ka"
                            ><w>cʼveta</w>
                        <gloss><q>drop (v)</q></gloss></mentioned> (melting, "dripping" glaciers are
                    known to give rise to mountain rivers). The loss of %iv%i before %ii%i,%ie%i is
                    regular, cf. <ref type="xr" target="#entry_ḱʼīrī"/> | %ikʼere%i ‘pie’←
                        <mentioned xml:lang="ka"><lang/>
                        <w>kʼveri</w></mentioned>, <ref type="xr" target="#entry_kʼela"/> ‘bench’ ←
                        <mentioned xml:lang="xmf"><lang/>
                        <w>kʼvela</w></mentioned>, <ref type="xr" target="#entry_xīd"/> | %ixed%i
                    ‘sweat’ ← <mentioned xml:lang="x-oldirn"><lang/>
                        <w>xvaida-</w></mentioned>, <ref type="xr" target="#entry_xī"/> | %iхе%i
                    ‘own’ ← <mentioned xml:lang="x-oldirn"><lang/>
                        <w>xvai-</w></mentioned>, <ref type="xr" target="#entry_xīstær"/> |
                    %ixestær%i ‘elder’ = <mentioned xml:lang="sog"><lang/>
                        <w>xveštar</w></mentioned> etc.%n<bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_ОЯФ_I"
                            /><biblScope>51, 325</biblScope></bibl>.</etym>
            </entry>
